that I struggle to think of things I really want. Right now, I’m simply busy getting better. I want to go to a dance class! I hope to get to a yoga class or two. Significantly, I want to go to the beach. My doctor took away my copper ion bracelet because I’ve had poisoning this week and I’m guessing that my main catholicon is a connection between the earth (the sand) and the body. When I look out of the window toward the sea, it brings me peace and I want to be near it.

I have no regrets-I’ve had a wonderful life so far. I look forward to a beautiful love life. I want to take some photographs at a vineyard I’ve been asked to document. I want to ski some day soon-I love skiing. There is so much waiting for me.

Golf is not a sport, doing a wheelie on a bike is not a sport and going to the toilet is not a sport, so unless someone says your snooker is a sport, it can’t be a sport-ellie mccarthy
